The paper presents a machine learning approach for patient monitoring in ICUs, which involves identifying the state-of-health of a patient given their observed vital signs using a discriminative classifier. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
